If your machine doesn't have a ".ssh" folder, from "Home" right click and select New Folder. Name it .ssh
download the file named: id_rsa from github and drag it into your newly created .ssh folder

open terminal and type:

ssh -L 59000:localhost:5901 -C -N -l ubuntu [your assigned ip address]  ex: 10.50.23.55

press enter. This will establish the tunnel to the VM  [DO NOT CLOSE THE TERMINAL!!!]


use Remmina to remotely access your VM. Select VNC at the drop down and type: 
localhost:59000    (this will connect to the destination port 5901)

VNC password: Jetpack1!  (you can save this password)

to exit the VM session, press CTRL C on the terminal window.
